pull_request.body:
https://github.com/AdguardTeam/AdguardFilters/issues/152341.
Sometimes an old rule does not work at all in Firefox (AdGuard for Windows).
The new rule sometimes fails on the first run of the page for some unknown reason, but always works afterwards.
You can also set a variable `uc_user_interaction` with a value `true` in localStorage, but there is a problem with the first launch of the page.
```javascript
AG_onLoad(function() {
    var a = new MutationObserver(function() {
        var hostElement = document.getElementById('usercentrics-root');
        var shadowRoot = hostElement.shadowRoot;
        if (hostElement && shadowRoot) {
            var shadowElement = shadowRoot.querySelector('button[data-testid="uc-accept-all-button"]');
            if (!shadowElement) return;
            shadowElement.click();
        };
    });
    a.observe(document, {
        childList: !0,
        subtree: !0,
        attributeFilter: ["style"]
    });
    setTimeout(function() {
        a.disconnect()
    }, 3E4)
});
```

